National Team Trials kicks off today in Austin with the Women’s Boulder/Lead Qualification ➡️ Follow along on my story for livestream links and results‼️

Boulder/Lead National Team ✅

This one means a lot. After a few years of leaving the team selection events feeling unsatisfied, it feels really good to walk away having qualified for the World Cup season. 
The interplay between confidence and doubt, energy and fatigue, excitement and frustration was ever-present and exhausting throughout this entire competition - thankful for those who helped me manage those emotions and focus on the present moment 🤍

🥂 to another season of feeling all the emotions that climbing has to bring. 
lots of appreciation for everyone on this @usaclimbing 🇺🇸 team… psyched to travel with, and learn from, you all ❤️‍🔥

Japan bound ✈️🇯🇵 with @brookeclimbs 💞

The World Cup season is coming up quick… I’m this excited ⬆️🎥

First World Cup of the season has come and gone. This event was a great reminder of why I love this sport: the people, the places, the playfulness… 

Hoping I can connect the dots and better express myself on the wall next week ➡️ I’m looking ahead at the season with my heart full and lots of motivation… Korea World Cup starts next weekend, but first I’m going to enjoy the last few days of training and exploring in Japan 🍱🇯🇵

First Word Cup win for @brookeclimbs 🥇🤯 Beyond happy for you… your attitude and work-ethic is such a tremendous source of inspiration for everyone around you, so so well deserved ❤️

The learning and adjusting continues after narrowly missing another Semifinal here in Brixen… Although I’ve had a frustrating season thus far, it’s been inspiring to see so many amazing stories play out on the World Cup stage recently.

I’m motivated and am excited to roll the dice for the final Boulder World Cup of the year in Innsbruck 🇦🇹🎲

Thankful for all the people and moments which made this trip 🇨🇿🇦🇹🇮🇹🇧🇬🇨🇭so memorable 🤍

I decided to skip Chamonix and Briançon (snif 😢) 
in order to make the necessary adjustments before competing in Boulders at the World Championships in Bern later this summer 📆

Hoping that a few days off the wall followed by a bouldering tune-up 🛠️ will just be what I need for the mental/physical to align 🔄 and allow me to find my flow again 🚀✨

📸: @vladek_zumr

At the last World Champs in Moscow I competed only in Lead and remember watching Bouldering hoping that I’d get a chance to compete on the blocs next time around…

⏰🔄 Fast forward two years and I’m headed to my second World Championships 🇨🇭, with a Bouldering ticket 🎟️ this time! I’ve had to adjust the final preparations (psa don’t drop heavy objects on your toes) but feeling confident that I will be able make it work and enjoy the moment ✨ 

10pts if you can guess what I dropped on my foot🦶⬇️

World Champs: P29 
Felt good to find some flow 🌀 and feel like I was in the game 🎲 despite a rocky few weeks 🤕 #ninetoeclo
So much to take away for next season and I’m ending this event hungry for more 🫑🚂
